- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses differentially private mechanisms and privacy metrics. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper applies the mechanisms to the subgraph counting problem and the linear query problem. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as differential privacy is often used in machine learning applications. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possibility as the paper discusses metrics and mappings between metric spaces. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also a possibility as the paper discusses mechanisms for protecting privacy in data sharing.
